ight Marsha Norman. At once startling, engrossing, suspenseful, and exhilarating, Nabers's powerful drama employs a real-life nightmare, the Atlanta Child Murders of the late 1970s, to incisively examine human frailty and the prickly complexities of a mother-daughter relationship. A stunning theatrical work, both thoughtful and profoundly moving, Serial Black Face is richly deserving of this year's prize.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Feb 2020) 0aAfrican AmericansxDrama. 7aDRAMA / American.2bisacsh1 aNorman, Marsha08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook Package 2014-2015z978311067250340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300216509423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/doc/cover/9780300216509.jpg  a978-3-11-067250-3  YUP eBook Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aEBA_FAO